<h2>Â Swing Doors</h2>
Solar offers several side-hinged swing door options that can be customized with decorative glass or wood veneer and are ideal for interior and exterior applications.Â While Swing Doors may be one of the simplest and most common door systems, they should not be overlooked when designing and planning out a residential or commercial space. Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> swing door systems are ideal for front doors, patio doors, entry doors, interior doors, and they can also be retrofitted into already existing structures. With numerous custom decorative glazing, finish, and matching sidelite and transom options, these Swing Doors can either blend in with the aesthetics of a surrounding structure, acting as utilitarian entrances, or they can be the star of the show, with the grandeur of a true entry door.
<h3>Options:</h3>
<ul>
 	<li>Single Doors / Terrace Doors</li>
 	<li>Double Doors / French Doors</li>
 	<li>Single Dutch Doors</li>
 	<li>French Dutch Doors</li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="size-full wp-image-36969 alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Swing-Res.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Residential Swing Doors</h2>
Swing Doors create an ideal entryway or interior door in residential applications. With matching transoms and sidelites, as well as complete mulling options with operable windows, swing doors can create a grand entrance. Traditional flair can be added with a French door with passive hardware sets, or a sleek modern aesthetic with a combination of window &amp; door sizes all utilizing the same framing.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="size-full wp-image-36949 alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Swing-Comm.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Commercial Swing Doors</h2>
Our Swing Doors create a thermally enhanced entrance to any business. Commercial systems can be ADA compliant and equipped with standard push/pull hardware and locking mechanisms. Panic hardware is also available upon request. Commercial terrace doors are often used in hotels, restaurants, and clothing boutiques. Solar InnovationsÂ® can also provide screen systems for our commercial exterior doors.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="wp-image-37010 size-full alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Swing-Terr2.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Terrace Doors</h2>
Terrace Doors, or single swing doors, are a single panel opening used in both internal and external applications. Terrace Doors are commonly used in both commercial and residential applications as entrance doors. They are also a convenient addition to a Folding Glass Wall, Slide &amp; Stack Glass Wall, or other operable wall as a point of entry without operating the entire unit.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="size-full wp-image-36947 alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Swing-French.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>French Doors</h2>
French Doors, also known as a dual swing doors or double swing doors, consist of two door panels that close in the center. French Doors do not require framing between the two panels, providing an unobstructed opening. These classic doors are commonly used in traditional structures and business entryways. Passive hardware sets are available for an elegant mirrored appearance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="size-full wp-image-36964 alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Swing-Dutch.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Dutch Doors</h2>
Dutch doors, also known as split doors, half doors, barn-style doors, and stable doors, consist of two independent panel doors stacked atop one another. With Dutch Doors, the top panel can be opened while the bottom panel remains closed, making them ideal for childcare facilities or any location with animals. Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup>â€™ Dutch Doors are available in single and French door configurations and can be all glass, glass upper panels with solid lower panels, or all solid panels.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter wp-image-37031 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/terrace-door-custom.png" alt="Custom designed front door" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Custom Options</h2>
Custom sizes and mulled configurations are available. Fully custom doors can be designed as well, including custom shapes or archways.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="size-full wp-image-36970 alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Swing-Terr-1.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Mulled Capabilities</h2>
Swing Doors feature similar panel and hardware design as Solar InnovationsÂ® operable walls and structures, creating a consistent appearance throughout any project. Our terrace and French doors are designed to be seamlessly integrated into several different door, window, mulled, and operable systems, including the European, Mulled, and International window systems, which will provide matching sightlines and create one cohesive unit.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36820 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/thermal-break-icon-small-1.png" alt="" width="150" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Thermally Enhanced</h2>
The thermal break separates the aluminum and minimizes conductivity of heat and cold from the inside to the outside to ensure a structureâ€™s interior remains comfortable at any time of year.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37450" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/coastal-icon.png" alt="" width="91" height="102" /><span style="font-size: 16px;">Â </span></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Coastal Applications</h2>
Our systems have the option to be both coastal and non-coastal. By using stainless steel hardware our hardware and material withstands the corrosive effects of the elements in these coastal regions.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36902 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/hardware-icon.png" alt="" width="86" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Vertical Integration</h2>
Solar manufactures not only its products but also many of the components it uses for the hardware. This allows us to better control lead times to help server our customers better.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36903 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/recylcled-material-icon.png" alt="" width="102" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Sustainable Products</h2>
Solarâ€™s products are manufactured with outstanding thermal performance, durable framework, and sustainable materials making it a great option for your next project.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2>Configurations &amp; Operations</h2>
Terrace, French, Dutch, and French Dutch configurations are all available. Swing Doors can be inswing or outswing and are available in custom sizes. Oversize doors are available with engineering approval.

